{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"360h–1","heading":"Program to improve the device recall system","label":"360h–1 Program to improve the device recall system","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360h–1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/ch9/schV/ptA","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs360h%E2%80%931","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2016—Subsecs. (c), (d). redesignated subsec. (d) as (c) and struck out former subsec. (c). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary shall document the basis for the termination by the Food and Drug Administration of a device recall.”Pub. L. 114–255"],"amendments":["Amendments2016—Subsecs. (c), (d). redesignated subsec. (d) as (c) and struck out former subsec. (c). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary shall document the basis for the termination by the Food and Drug Administration of a device recall.”Pub. L. 114–255"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360h–1/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360h–1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs360h%E2%80%931%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360h–1/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s360h–1/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs360h%E2%80%931%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"establish a program to routinely and systematically assess information relating to device recalls and use such information to proactively identify strategies for mitigating health risks presented by defective or unsafe devices;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph